  "body": "We currently have a suite of [Echidna tests](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/24edceb652b5a812313b0b742f74acaa0f3ea3a5/packages/contracts-bedrock/contracts/echidna) in our `contracts-bedrock` package which use Echidna for property testing. \r\n\r\nWe also have a suite of forge [invariant tests](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/24edceb652b5a812313b0b742f74acaa0f3ea3a5/packages/contracts-bedrock/contracts/test/invariants). \r\n\r\nIn order to standardize our tooling, we'd like to convert the echidna tests over to Forge invariant tests. External contributors would be very welcome here. \r\n\r\nA suggested workflow would be to open one PR per converted test file: \r\n\r\n- [ ] FuzzAddressAliasing.sol\r\n- [ ] FuzzBurn.sol\r\n- [ ] FuzzEncoding.sol\r\n- [ ] FuzzHashing.sol\r\n- [ ] FuzzOptimismPortal.sol\r\n- [ ] FuzzResourceMetering.sol\r\n\r\nThe first 4 files listed are much simpler to work with, so I'd suggest starting from the top.",
